apple-bacon-cheddar-quesadilla.title: Apple, bacon, cheddar quesadilla
apple-bacon-cheddar-quesadilla.description: A fun twist on the quesadilla
apple-bacon-cheddar-quesadilla.ingredients:
1 tortilla
2 strips bacon, cooked
1/4 apple, thin sliced
2 ounces grated cheddar cheese
1 tablespoon butter or lard
apple-bacon-cheddar-quesadilla.instructiions:
Heat the fat in a pan over medium low
When the fat is melted, lay the tortilla flat in the pan and cover evenly with cheddar
When the cheese is melted, lay the bacon and apple slices over one half of the tortilla, fold, and remove.
apple-bacon-cheddar-quesadilla.imageAlt: A cast-iron skillet containing an open-faced quesadilla cooking with bacon and apple slices on top.
apple-bacon-cheddar-quesadilla.source: Something I threw together on a whim. It has good textures and flavors. I made it with a cosmic crisp apple. I'd like to try a granny smith.

boiled-broccoli.title: Boiled Broccoli
boiled-broccoli.description: A quick, substantial vegetable side dish
boiled-broccoli.instructiions:
Bring two quarts (or litres) of generously salted water to a vigorous boil.
Boil broccoli florets for one minute and 45 seconds.
Drain away water through a collander or strainer.
Cool briefly before serving.
boiled-broccoli.imageAlt: A large pot of broccoli steaming and boiling on a stovetop
boiled-broccoli.source: This is the laziest, fastest way I know to cook broccoli satisfactorily

boiled-carrots.title: Boiled Carrots
boiled-carrots.ingredients:
2 cups of 3/4 inch chopped carrots
salt (optional)
boiled-carrots.instructiions:
Bring two quarts (or litres) of water to a vigorous boil. Salt if desired.
Boil chopped carrots for two minutes.
Drain away water through a collander or strainer.
Allow to cool before serving.
boiled-carrots.imageAlt: A large bowl of steaming, just-cooked carrot pieces.
boiled-carrots.source: This is the laziest, fastest way I know to cook carrots satisfactorily

chocolate-chip-cookies.title: Chocolate chip cookies
chocolate-chip-cookies.ingredients:
1 cup salted butter, softened
1 cup white (granulated) sugar
1 cup light brown sugar, packed
1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract
2 large eggs
3 cups all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon baking soda
1/2 teaspoon baking powder
1 teaspoon sea salt
12 ounces chocolate chips
chocolate-chip-cookies.instructiions:
Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Line a baking pan with parchment paper and set aside.
In a separate bowl mix flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder. Set aside.
Cream together butter and sugars until combined.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Mix in the dry ingredients until combined.
Add 12 oz package of chocolate chips and mix well.
Roll 2-3 TBS (depending on how large you like your cookies) of dough at a time into balls and place them evenly spaced on your prepared cookie sheets. (alternately, use a small cookie scoop to make your cookies).
Bake in preheated oven for approximately 8-10 minutes. Take them out when they are just BARELY starting to turn brown.
Let them sit on the baking pan for 2 minutes before removing to cooling rack.
chocolate-chip-cookies.imageAlt: Freshly baked chocolate-chip cookies on a wooden countertop surrounded by choclate chips, chunks and other ingredients.

chocolate-mousse.title: Chocolate Mousse
chocolate-mousse.ingredients:
1½ cups chocolate chips
½ cup prepared espresso coffee
½ cup Grand Marnier
4 egg yolks
2 cups heavy cream
1/4 cup sugar
8 egg whites
Pinch of salt
½ teaspoon vanilla
chocolate-mousse.instructiions:
Melt chocolate chips in a heavy saucepan over very low heat, stirring.
Add espresso coffee. Stir in liqueur. Cool to room temperature.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition until thickened.
Whip 1 cup of cream until stiff. Gradually beat in sugar, beating until stiff. Beat egg yolks with salt until stiff. Gently beat egg whites into cream.
Fold egg whites into cream.
Stir about 1/3 of cream and egg mixture thoroughly into chocolate mixture. Then scrape remaining cream and egg mixture over lightened chocolate base and fold together gently.
Pour into individual dessert cups or serving bowl. Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Serve with other cup of whipped cream, whipped.
chocolate-mousse.imageAlt: An image of a dessert setting featuring individual glass cups of chocolate mousse with whipped cream on top, each garnished with a mint leaf and espresso beans. A silver espresso maker, a white teapot, and a bottle of Grand Marnier are in the background, on a table with a white floral-patterned tablecloth. Each cup is on a small plate with a spoon beside it, under soft, warm lighting.
chocolate-mousse.source: This recipe is from the kitchen of Pat Stansell and serves 8 or more. The quote by Alexander Pope at the end reads, ""

chocolate-peanut-butter-protein-drink.title: Chocolate, peanut butter protein drink
chocolate-peanut-butter-protein-drink.ingredients:
1 cup fat free milk
1 scoop chocolate protein powder
1 tablespoon peanut powder
1 teaspoon allulose
1 pinch salt
chocolate-peanut-butter-protein-drink.instructiions: Combine all ingredients in a shaker bottle and shake until combined
chocolate-peanut-butter-protein-drink.imageAlt: A peanut butter chocolate protien shake in a shaker bottle surrounded by ingredients like chocolate squares, peanuts and milk.
chocolate-peanut-butter-protein-drink.source: I take credit (and blame) for this recipe. It results from my love/hate relationship with chocolate peanut butter flavored desserts.

egg-tarts.title: Egg Tarts
egg-tarts.ingredients:
11 tablespoons unsalted butter
1/2 cup granulated sugar
1/2 teaspoon salt
1 large egg
1 1/2 cups all purpose flour
1/2 cup granulated sugar
1/2 teaspoon cornstarch
1/8 teaspoon salt
3/4 cup milk
2/3 cup heavy cream
8 egg yolks
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
egg-tarts.instructiions:
Adjust oven rack to lower-middle position, place baking stone or sheet pan on rack, and heat oven to 375°. Lightly grease a 12 cup muffin tin. Stir butter, sugar, and salt in a large bowl until combined. Stir in egg, and then flour until completely combined. Divide dough into 16 portions and roll into balls.
Press a dough ball into each cup, pressing dough up sides to about 1/4 inch from top of cup, and maintaining a thickness about 1/8-inch thick. Chill for 30 minutes.
Whisk sugar, cornstarch, and salt in a medium bowl. Whisk in milk, cream, yolks, and vanilla until combined.
Fill each cup with custard to about 1/8-inch from top of crust (don't overfill). Bake until crust is golden and custard is just set, about 20 minutes. Let tarts cool in pan for 15 minutes then carefully transfer to wire rack to cool. Let pan cool, then repeat with remaining dough and custard. Serve room temperature or chilled.
egg-tarts.imageAlt: 14 golden-brown egg tarts in tins on a baking sheet.

green-bean-casserole.title: Green Bean Casserole
green-bean-casserole.ingredients:
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 medium onion, thinly sliced
Kosher salt, freshly ground black pepper
1 pound mushrooms, such as cremini, button, oyster or maitake, quartered
1 pound green beans, stems trimmed, cut in half or coarsely chopped, if you like
2 tablespoons unsalted butter
2 tablespoons flour
1 3/4 cups whole milk
2 tablespoons soy sauce or tamari
1 clove garlic, finely grated or chopped
An undetermined amount of French’s Onions, from the container
green-bean-casserole.instructiions:
Heat olive oil in a large (at least 8”) skillet over medium–high heat. Add onions and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally (I use a wooden spoon this whole time), until they start to soften and brown, 10–12 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium, add mushrooms and season again with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally until they shrink, soften, brown and concentrate their flavors, another 10–12 minutes (the onions will be very dark and caramelized at this point, too, which is what we want).
Add green beans (the skillet will be a little full now, but just give it time, the green beans will soften and shrink as they cook), season with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until they’re bright green and totally tender, 8–10 minutes.
Add butter and let it melt in the skillet. Sprinkle flour over everything and stir for 2 or 3 minutes to toast in the fat and browned bits of the skillet. Slowly add milk, letting it thicken between stirs, until it’s all added. Add soy sauce and garlic, stirring to blend. Let the gravy come to a simmer, thickening in the skillet around the vegetables, making sure everything is evenly dispersed and coated. Season again with salt and more pepper.
Preheat oven to 425°. Top green beans and mushrooms with French’s Onions from a container and bake until golden brown and bubbly around the edges, 20–25 minutes.
green-bean-casserole.imageAlt: A casserole dish on a counter containing a green bean, mushroom casserole with fried onions over the top.

chinese-hot-oil-noodles.title: Chinese hot oil noodles - 油泼面
chinese-hot-oil-noodles.description: A fragrant noodle dish, bursting with flavor
chinese-hot-oil-noodles.ingredients:
4 ounces dried wheat noodles
1 handful of leafy greens (choy sum, spinach, or baby bok choy)
1 teaspoon light soy sauce
1 teaspoon dark soy sauce
1/2 teaspoon Chinese black vinegar
red pepper flakes
salt
chopped scallion
chopped cilantro
2 cloves garlic
2 1/2 tablespoons oil
chinese-hot-oil-noodles.instructiions:
Boil the noodles according to package directions until al dente. In the same pot, blanch the leafy greens until cooked through. Drain.
Add the cooked noodles and greens to a heatproof bowl, along with the light soy sauce, dark soy sauce, vinegar, crushed red pepper flakes, salt, scallion, cilantro, and minced garlic.
In a small pot, heat the oil until shimmering. Carefully pour the hot oil over the bowl of noodles, and mix everything together. Serve!
chinese-hot-oil-noodles.imageAlt: A hot bowl of noodles and vegetables, surrounded by small dishes of peppercorns and salt.

hummus.title: Hummus
hummus.ingredients:
1 can chickpeas, drained
4 ounces tahini
salt
hummus.instructiions: Combine chickpeas and tahini in a food processor. Use water to create the correct consistency if needed. Add salt to taste.
hummus.imageAlt: a bowl of creamy, freshly made hummus

middle-eastern-vegetable-salad.title: Middle eastern vegetable salad
middle-eastern-vegetable-salad.ingredients:
10 scallions, white and green parts, thinly sliced
1 pound ripe tomatoes, seeded, cored, and ½-inch-diced
1 hothouse cucumber, halved lengthwise, seeded, and ½-inch-diced
1 can or jar (12 to 16 ounces) chickpeas, rinsed and drained
1/3 cup chopped fresh parsley
1/3 cup chopped fresh mint leaves
1/3 cup julienned fresh basil leaves
1/2 cup freshly squeezed lemon juice
1 tablespoon minced garlic
Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper
1/2 cup good olive oil
8 ounces good feta cheese, ½-inch-diced
Toasted pita bread, for serving
middle-eastern-vegetable-salad.instructiions:
Place the scallions, tomatoes, cucumber, chickpeas, parsley, mint, and basil in a large salad bowl and toss to combine.
In a small bowl or measuring cup, whisk together the lemon juice, garlic, 2 teaspoons salt, and 1 teaspoon pepper. Slowly whisk in the olive oil to make an emulsion. Pour the dressing over the salad, tossing gently to coat all the vegetables. Add the feta, sprinkle with salt and pepper, and toss gently. Serve the salad with the toasted pita bread.
middle-eastern-vegetable-salad.imageAlt: An over-the-top rendering of a chickpea, tomato, cucumber and feta salad.

oven-baked-asparagus.title: Oven baked asparagus
oven-baked-asparagus.description: Asparagus with good flavor and texture
oven-baked-asparagus.ingredients:
1 pound asparagus, woody ends removed
1 clove garlic, minced
1/2 lemon, juiced
salt
pepper
olive oil
parmesan cheese
oven-baked-asparagus.instructiions:
Pre heat oven to 400° F; 205° C.
Spread asparagus in an optionally foil lined baking sheet. Drizzle with olive oil. Distribute garlic. Roll asparagus to coat.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and parmesan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until asparagus is approaching your preferred texture. It will keep cooking once removed from the oven.
Drizzle lemon juice and serve.
oven-baked-asparagus.imageAlt: A tray of uncooked asparagus on an oven rack. An obviously incorrect (machine-generated) temperature display reads 400°F 405°C (should be 205°C).

bacon-cheddar-broccoli-egg-bites.title: Bacon, cheddar, broccoli egg bites
bacon-cheddar-broccoli-egg-bites.description: A high protein, low calorie bacon, cheddar, broccoli egg bite recipe
bacon-cheddar-broccoli-egg-bites.ingredients:
1 cup egg whites
1 tablespoon corn starch
1 cup broccoli florets chopped
2 strips cooked bacon chopped
4 ounces grated fat free cheddar
1/4 teaspoon black pepper
bacon-cheddar-broccoli-egg-bites.instructiions:
Pre-heat oven to 400° F, 205 C
In a mixing bowl, gently whisk corn starch into egg whites
Mix remaining ingredients into egg white mixture
Spoon mixture into a nonstick muffin tin, taking care to distribute liquid and solid ingredients evenly. Avoid filling cups over 2/3 full - mixture will expand while cooking.
Cook approximately 20 minutes
bacon-cheddar-broccoli-egg-bites.imageAlt: Bacon, cheddar, broccoli, salt and various kitchen implements displayed in an artistic manner.
bacon-cheddar-broccoli-egg-bites.source: This recipe is the result of my efforts to make a lower calorie, higher protein version of Starucks's egg bites. These come out dry and spongy (likely because I've been mixing the ingredints in a blender). In my ideal recipe, they would have a custardy texture. I'm considering adding some egg yolks.

rice-and-beans.title: Rice and Beans
rice-and-beans.description: An affordable rice and beans recipe from Paul Graham's essay 'Ramen Profitable'
rice-and-beans.ingredients:
olive oil or butter
1 onion yellow onion
other fresh vegetables; experiment
3 cloves garlic
1 can white, kidney, or black beans
1 cube Knorr beef or vegetable bouillon
1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper
3 teaspoons ground cumin
1 cup dry rice, preferably brown
rice-and-beans.instructiions:
Put rice in rice cooker. Add water as specified on rice package. (Default: 2 cups water per cup of rice.) Turn on rice cooker and forget about it.
Chop onions and other vegetables and fry in oil, over fairly low heat, till onions are glassy. Put in chopped garlic, pepper, cumin, and a little more fat, and stir. Keep heat low. Cook another 2 or 3 minutes, then add beans (don't drain the beans), and stir. Throw in the bouillon cube(s), cover, and cook on lowish heat for at least 10 minutes more. Stir vigilantly to avoid sticking.
If you want to save money, buy beans in giant cans from discount stores. Spices are also much cheaper when bought in bulk. If there's an Indian grocery store near you, they'll have big bags of cumin for the same price as the little jars in supermarkets.
rice-and-beans.imageAlt: A bowl with rice and beans garnished with cilantro rests on a table
rice-and-beans.source: The recipe appears in the essay Ramen Profitable by Paul Graham under the title Rice and Beans for 2n.

slow-roasted-sweet-potatoes.title: Slow Roasted Sweet Potatoes
slow-roasted-sweet-potatoes.description: A delicious and healthy side dish
slow-roasted-sweet-potatoes.ingredients:
sweet potatoes
olive oil
salt
black pepper
slow-roasted-sweet-potatoes.instructiions:
Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C)
Wash and scrub the sweet potatoes
Puncture potatoes with a fork several times
Coat potatoes with olive oil, salt and pepper
Wrap potatoes in aluminum foil
Bake for two hours on a cookie sheet
slow-roasted-sweet-potatoes.imageAlt: A baking sheet filled with golden brown oven roasted sweet potatoes.
slow-roasted-sweet-potatoes.source: A simple and healthy recipe for oven roasted sweet potatoes.

vegetable-gratin.title: Vegetable Gratin
vegetable-gratin.description: A browned, cheese-crusted vegetable side dish
vegetable-gratin.ingredients:
good olive oil
1 onion, thin sliced
1 Japanese eggplant, thin sliced
1 zucchini, thin sliced
1 potato, thin sliced
parmesan cheese, grated
salt
pepper
vegetable-gratin.instructiions:
Pre-heat the oven to 375° F; 190° C
Coat a medium to deep oven dish with olive oil. Layer half of the vegetables, in an alternating pattern, covering the bottom of the dish. The more snugly slices lay together, the less likely they will be to bake into vegetable crisps. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and drizzle with olive oil.
Repeat with the remaining vegetables, building and seasoning a second layer.
Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake for 30 - 35 minutes. Remove the dish carefully, discarding foil. Cover generously with parmesan cheese.
Replace dish in the oven and continue baking 20 minutes until cheese is golden brown. Serve hot. Reheats well.
vegetable-gratin.imageAlt: A casserole dish containing vegetable gratin rests on a table surrounded by parmesan cheese, olive oil, zucchini, onion, and a spoonfull of salt
